# Galao System — Cursor Rules
# These rules guide AI suggestions throughout this project.

## Project Purpose
Galao is an intraday futures trading LEARNING PLATFORM.
Goal: collect structured trade data to A/B test bracket sizes and line strengths.
P&L optimization comes later. Data correctness is the priority now.

## Hard Rules (never violate)
- Trading ALWAYS uses the PAPER port (4002). Never submit orders to the LIVE port.
- LIVE port (4001) is for market data and historical data ONLY.
- Components communicate via SQLite DB only — no direct inter-process calls or imports between Decider/Broker/Fetcher.
- Every Python script must implement a `--self-test` flag.
- All changes must be noted in docs/release_notes.md.
- Brackets are always symmetric. Any positive size is allowed.
- Config values are never hardcoded — all tunables live in config.yaml.
- Entry orders are LMT (Limit) — bounce strategy. Do NOT use STP for entry.

## Architecture
- decider.py       — generates commands at day open, handles replenishment, triggers shutdown
- broker.py        — executes IB orders, updates DB with status (dumb executor only)
- fetcher.py       — downloads historical CSV data via LIVE port only
- visualizer/      — browser dashboard: DB viewer, live orders, prices, P&L, connection status
- analyzer.py      — A/B test engine [LATER — do not build yet]
- lib/db.py        — ALL DB access goes through here
- lib/ib_client.py — ib_insync connection wrapper with client ID pool
- lib/order_builder.py — OCO bracket order construction (LMT entry + LMT TP + STP SL)
- lib/config_loader.py — loads config.yaml

## IB Connections
- LIVE:  host=127.0.0.1, port=4001, client_ids=[101,102,103]
- PAPER: host=127.0.0.1, port=4002, client_ids=[201,301,401]
- Connect by trying each client ID in pool until one succeeds
- Always disconnect cleanly (atexit handler)

## Critical Lines
- File: data/critical_lines/levels_daily_YYYYMMDD.txt
- Format: SYMBOL, PRICE, STRENGTH  (e.g. MES, 6250, 3)
- Strength: 1-3 (1=weak, 3=strong) — recorded for A/B testing, does not affect order logic
- Per line: LMT BUY + LMT SELL, each with N bracket sizes from config

## Order Logic — Toggle Rule
Entry order type depends on current price vs line price. Evaluated at command generation AND replenishment.

| Current price vs line | BUY entry | SELL entry |
|-----------------------|-----------|------------|
| Price ABOVE line      | LMT BUY   | STP SELL   |
| Price BELOW line      | STP BUY   | LMT SELL   |

- All prices rounded to nearest 0.25 (MES tick size) at Decider, before writing to DB
- Max 1 contract per order (learning phase)
- Replenishment re-evaluates toggle based on current price

## Position Management
- Stagnation kill-switch: position open > stagnation_seconds (60) AND price moved < stagnation_min_move_points (0.5) → market exit, log STAGNATION
- SL cool-down: after SL hit, disarm line for sl_cooldown_seconds (30) before replenishing
- All three values are configurable in config.yaml under position:

## DB
- File: data/galao.db
- WAL mode on every connection, busy_timeout=5000ms
- Each process opens its own connection — never share across threads/processes
- Every command record must store: bracket_size, line_strength, line_price, symbol — for A/B testing

## A/B Testing
- Two test variables: bracket_size (from config) and line_strength (from critical lines file)
- No runtime decisions based on these — record only
- Analyzer (future) will process DB data

## Coding Workflow (mandatory before declaring complete)
1. Copy current file to versions/{filename}.{YYYYMMDD_HHMM} before editing
2. Make changes
3. Run --self-test → must pass
4. Write release notes entry to DB (program, version, change_type, description)
5. Only then: announce complete

## Logging
- Use lib/logger.py for all logging
- All levels: DEBUG / INFO / WARNING / ERROR / CRITICAL
- Log format: {timestamp_utc} | {level} | {component} | {message}
- Every IB interaction: minimum INFO
- Log files: logs/{component}.log

## Error Handling
- IB disconnect: retry 5x over 5 minutes (60s between), then abort
- DB write fail: log to file, abort
- Abort = trigger shutdown if session active, then exit

## Code Structure
- Max 500 lines per file — split if exceeded
- lib/ is flat, one concern per file
- versions/ folder: never edit files there

## Startup
- preflight.py runs before any session: LIVE port, PAPER port, price fetch, DB test
- Any failure = hard abort

## What NOT to suggest
- Do not use STP orders for entry (that's V1 breakout strategy — wrong for Galao)
- Do not send orders to the LIVE port
- Do not mock the IB connection in production code paths
- Do not share SQLite connections across threads/processes
- Do not build the Analyzer yet
- Do not add features beyond what is asked
- Do not hardcode port numbers, client IDs, or bracket sizes
